│ handling is consistent between the original code and fabs. However, the current code doesn't check for NoNaNs flags before performing this                │
│ transformation. The fabs intrinsic always preserves NaN payloads but clears the sign bit, while the original select preserves the exact input value       │
│ (including sign bit) when the comparison is false (as happens with SNaN).\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The fix is to add a NoNaNs check to the first     │
│ pattern in foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs. Specifically, lines 2796-2804 should only perform the transformation if the select instruction has NoNaNs semantics, │
│ which ensures that NaN inputs don't need to be preserved exactly. This matches the later pattern in the same function (lines 2840-2841) which correctly   │
│ requires both NoSignedZeros and NoNaNs.\n\n5. Conclusion: By requiring NoNaNs for the fabs transformation in the fsub pattern, we ensure that the         │
│ transformation is only applied when NaN semantics don't matter, preventing the incorrect handling of SNaN values. This will make the transformation       │
│ semantically correct while still allowing the optimization in cases where NoNaNs is guaranteed."})                                                        │
